title: Locals Teams Advance to 7A, 7AA Finals
text:
Locals Teams Advance to 7A, 7AA Finals 
By Zach Schneider October 20, 2015 Updated Oct 20, 2015 at 10:46 PM CDT 
(NNCNOW.com) --- The matchups are set for the Section 7A and 7AA boys' and girls' soccer championships, and there are four Northland teams still alive in the quest for a berth in the MSHSL tournament. 
Hermantown will face Cloquet-Esko-Carlton in the Section 7A boys' final, with that match scheduled for 7:00 p.m. Thursday at Public Schools Stadium. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
The Hermantown girls also advanced to the Section 7A final, where they will face Princeton at 7:00 p.m. Thursday in Chisago Lakes, Minn. 
In Section 7AA, the Duluth East boys advanced to the championship and will face Anoka at 7:00 p.m. Thursday in Anoka, Minn.
